in this company.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following represents the most appropriate management of this potential conflict of interest?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cancel the research project due to the conflict","Disclose share ownership to ethics committee only","Disclose conflict of interest to all relevant parties","Sell shares before submitting ethics application","Transfer shares to an immediate family member"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edisclose conflict of interest to all relevant parties\u003C/strong\u003E. This includes the human research ethics committee, study participants, and in any subsequent publications. While having shares constitutes a conflict of interest, it does not automatically invalidate the research if properly disclosed and managed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECancel the research project due to the conflict\u003C/strong\u003E - Having a conflict of interest does not automatically preclude conducting research if appropriately disclosed and managed\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisclose share ownership to ethics committee only\u003C/strong\u003E - Disclosure must extend beyond just the ethics committee to include participants and publications\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESell shares before submitting ethics application\u003C/strong\u003E - While this would eliminate the conflict, it is not necessary if the conflict is properly disclosed and managed\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransfer shares to an immediate family member\u003C/strong\u003E - This would be an attempt to conceal rather than properly manage the conflict of interest\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETransparency about conflicts of interest is essential for maintaining research integrity and public trust. The existence of a conflict does not necessarily compromise the research, but failure to disclose it does.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Conflicts of interest in research must be disclosed to ethics committees, participants, and in publications.","Share ownership in companies related to research constitutes a significant conflict of interest that requires disclosure."],"references":["Beauchamp TL, Childress JF. Principles of Biomedical Ethics. 8th ed. New York: Oxford University Press; 2019.","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94060"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18826"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94060","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94060"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-23T09:52:42+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-23T09:52:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11559"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111996"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data"